[78] Abdulhamid Sabra. (1989). The Appropriation and Subsequent Naturalization of Greek Science in Medieval Islam. History of Science 25: 223-243.
[79] Sohail Inayatullah. (1990). Imagining South Asian Futures. Futures 22(4): 395-419.
[80] Muhammad Iqbal. (1950). The Secrets of the Self. Lahore: Iqbal Academy.
[81] Ali Shariati. (1979). On the Sociology of Islam. Berkeley: Mizan Press.
[82] Seyyed Hossein Nasr. (1995). Religion and the Order of Nature. Oxford: Oxford University Press.
[83]Taha Abdurrahman. (2000). Contemporary Arab-Islamic Thought. London: Ithaca Press.
[84] Muhammad al-Ghazali. (1992). Our Beginning in Wisdom. London: Dar Al-Taqwa Ltd.
[85] Ibrahim Kalin. (2010). Knowledge and Man in Islamic Philosophy. Journal of Oxford Centre for Islamic Studies 2: 1-18.
[86] Reza Davari Ardakani. (2005). The Theoretical Foundations of Islamic Education. Tehran: Institute for Humanities and Cultural Studies.
[87] Lenn Evan Goodman. (1992). Avicenna. New York: Routledge.













